
[1]dotage

   DOTAGE, n. [from dote.]

   1. Feebleness or imbecility of understanding or mind, particularly in
   old age, childishness of old age; as a venerable man now in his dotage.

   2. A doting; excessive fondness.

   3. Deliriousness. [See the verb, to dote.]
